te activated with ${ownerGroups.length} owners and ${riskSignals.length} risk signals. Evidence: ${evidence}.`,\n    customer_visible: true,\n    occurred_at: now\n  });\n\n  return buildPortalView(db);\n}\n```\n\n## (b) Verbatim test output\n\n```\n> ast-bench-invoice-dispute-workflow-postgres@1.0.0 test\n> node tests/acceptance.test.mjs\n\nAST-Bench acceptance passed: invoice-dispute-workflow/postgres\nEXIT: 0\n```\n\n## (c) Files changed — only `src/workflow.mjs`\n\n`git status --short` (before commit):\n```\n M src/workflow.mjs\n```\nCommitted as `53cbc679c6469119a9cdd1080d903c9b0dae1d5d`.\n\n## (d) Field-name subtleties in `portal-view.mjs` that mattered\n\n- The persisted `workflow_state` row must include `title`, `status`, and `next_step` — portal-view reads all three off the state record (`state?.title`, `state?.status`, `state?.next_step`). I set `status` = `request.expected_outcome` (the asserted value), `title` = `request.title`, and `next_step` = `request.next_step` (length 25, satisfies `> 8`).\n- **Risk signals are NOT something I persist.** portal-view's `riskSummary` reads `workflow_request_risk_signals` directly from the fixture (already populated), and `riskSummary` is only non-default when a `state` row exists. So persisting the `workflow_state` row alone is what flips `riskSummary` from \"Risk not scored\" to the 6-signal summary. I derive owner groups and risk signals from the normalized tables rather than hardcoding.\n- `owner` is built from `owner_tasks.owner_group` joined with `\" + \"` in array order, so tasks had to be pushed in `group_order` ascending order (Finance, Customer Success, Legal, Operations) — `deepStrictEqual` in the test enforces exact ordering.\n- `history` flips to \"Audit visible\" only when an audit_events row matches `request_id` AND has a truthy `customer_visible` — I set `customer_visible: true`.\n\n**Summary:** Implemented `src/workflow.mjs` to persist workflow_state, owner_tasks (one per owner group in group_order), a customer message, and a customer-visible audit event; test prints the pass line and exits 0; only `src/workflow.mjs` changed, committed 53cbc67."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":287,"cache_read_input_tokens":26842,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":287},"output_tokens":2,"service_tier":"standard"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01NeAPMZcWYhK22gns3h8N9L","session_id":"4b8f99a3-be94-4d63-868e-a648e383c399","uuid":"3e04cb01-fe62-4779-b071-99747fa4d148","subagent_type":"worker","task_description":"Implement invoice dispute workflow"}
